= Create Crowd Collections By Agent Stage Material =
#context: lop
#type: node

"""Creates USD collections based on material binding names from an agent stage."""

== Overview ==

Create Crowd Collections By Agent Stage Material inspects the material bindings on the source agent stage (Input 2) and creates a corresponding USD collection for each unique material binding name. Collections are written to the target stage (Input 1).

This is designed for Houdini crowd workflows where each agent layer has material bindings that need to be exposed as USD collections for downstream look-dev or rendering.

@inputs

Input Stage:
    The destination USD stage where collections will be written.

Agent Stage w/ Materials Binding:
    The source agent stage containing material bindings to inspect.

@parameters

Collection:
    #id: collection_path
    Root prim path where collections will be created. Default: `/collections`.

From Path:
    #id: from_path
    Path within `agentdefinitions/agent/layers` to read material bindings from.

Replace Path:
    #id: replace_path
    Corresponding path in the materials source stage used to resolve binding names.
